{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1b2ba029-07e6-4a9b-86e8-040ea8664ad9","content":"In .NET 10, `dotnet test` uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform **by default** — you no longer need `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport`. That property was the .NET 9 opt-in bridge.\n\nYour setup is almost there. Just remove the now-unnecessary property:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_019qCt8Es5KKv1Cb5rmu1zgf","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Removing obsolete MTP property"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_013yQXgf7Zh5DSArFSuKHYEJ","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-67dc672965db4ae0a27f0962aaa3ca8a/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>","new_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-67dc672965db4ae0a27f0962aaa3ca8a/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"62cf298d-8f41-40e1-9432-b0c1c011b96a","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is on .NET 10 SDK (10.0.100) and using MSTest with `EnableMSTestRunner` and `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` set to true.\n\nIn .NET 10, `dotnet test` natively uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) as the default test runner. The `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property was needed in .NET 9 to opt into MTP support with `dotnet test`, but in .NET 10 it's no longer needed because MTP is the default.\n\nLet me provide the guidance:\n\n\nSince .NET 10 has MTP built in by default, they can safely remove `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` while keeping `EnableMSTestRunner` to maintain the test executable entry point.","outputTokens":526},"id":"0079f881-ca2d-4f43-ba6b-df5232bdc45d","timestamp":"2026-04-07T14:23:04.293Z","parentId":"4953a202-f55f-43a8-ac17-c5994ecfa747"}
